"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757271","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>Energy service providers could play an important role in delivering valuable services to consumers including, but not limited to, energy management, energy efficiency improvements and demand side response. The Government will continue to consider the role of energy service providers as the market for services they offer develops.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2017-09-12T13:35:05.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757271/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757271/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-05","Energy: Cost Effectiveness","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how they intend to ensure that energy service providers provide value for money for the consumer.","false","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone",,"Baroness Featherstone","HL1256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757272","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>The information requested is not held by the Department.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The General Medical Council (GMC) is the independent regulator of doctors in the United Kingdom. It has advised that from 1 September 2012 to 31 August 2017, the GMC has registered 117 refugee doctors. Of these doctors, currently 105 are registered, and 104 with a licence to practise.</p><p> </p><p>The GMC has informed us that the numbers of practising refugee doctors split per medical specialities are very small and could lead to identification of individuals, and we are therefore not providing this information.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:54:24.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757272/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757272/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757272/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Doctors: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many refugee doctors have been able to become registered by the General Medical Council in the last five years; and in which medical specialties those doctors are practicing.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL1257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757273","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>Health Education England (HEE) does not provide funding for programmes in Scotland and Wales. Funding for the requested programmes in England is shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Refugee doctor programme</p></td><td><p>HEE funding (2017/18)</p></td><td><p>Doctors currently enrolled in programme</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Reache North West (Salford)</p></td><td><p>£363,357</p></td><td><p>54</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Building Bridges (London)</p></td><td><p>£290,510</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North-East England (Stockton-on-Tees)</p></td><td><p>£63,180</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source: </em>HEE</p><p><em>Notes: </em>Data for Cardiff and Glasgow is not available as these programmes do not fall within HEE’s remit. Breakdown for the numbers of doctors currently enrolled on the Building Bridges programme (London) is not available.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:38:22.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757273/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757273/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Doctors: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many refugee doctors are currently enrolled in active refugee doctor programmes in the UK, specifically (1) Reache North West (Salford), (2) Building Bridges (London), (3) WARD (Cardiff), (4) The Bridges Programme (Glasgow) and (5) North-East England (Stockton-on-Tees); and how much annual funding each of those programmes receive from Health Education England.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL1258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757274","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Department does not collect these data. The Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman (PHSO) is independent of Government, being accountable to Parliament through the Public Administration and Constitutional Affairs Committee.</p><p> </p><p>This would be a matter for the PHSO to address.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:51:40.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757274/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757274/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757274/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many complaints were submitted about the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman in 2016; and what were the main themes of those complaints.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL1259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757275","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>The Government supports the development of a modern health and care workforce as part of the continuing drive to provide safe, accessible and high quality care for patients and service users.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department has developed proposals relating to the regulation of physician associates and remains committed to consulting on these in 2017.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:59:08.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757275/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757275/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757275/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Physician Associates: Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, in the light of remarks made by the Secretary of State for Health to the NHS Providers annual conference on 30 November 2016, when they will launch a consultation on the regulation of Physician Associate roles.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL1260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757276","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-19","<p>The behaviour of Bell Pottinger in South Africa has clearly been completely unacceptable. We welcome the investigations conducted by the Public Relations and Communications Association and Herbert Smith Freehills and the conclusions of their reports.</p><p>At no stage was Her Majesty's Government (HMG) in any way involved in this work, nor consulted in advance.</p><p>The UK has one of the world’s toughest anti-corruption laws, and HMG takes any allegations of bribery or corruption extremely seriously.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","HL1262 ; HL1263","2017-09-19T13:25:13.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757276/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757276/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757276/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-05","Bell Pottinger Group: South Africa","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of whether Bell Pottinger's recent public affairs work in South Africa was in line with their policy on international trade conducted by British firms.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757277","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-19","<p>The behaviour of Bell Pottinger in South Africa has clearly been completely unacceptable. We welcome the investigations conducted by the Public Relations and Communications Association and Herbert Smith Freehills and the conclusions of their reports.</p><p>At no stage was Her Majesty's Government (HMG) in any way involved in this work, nor consulted in advance.</p><p>The UK has one of the world’s toughest anti-corruption laws, and HMG takes any allegations of bribery or corruption extremely seriously.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","HL1261 ; HL1263","2017-09-19T13:25:14.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757277/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757277/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757277/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-05","Bell Pottinger Group: South Africa","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of whether the taking of income by UK Directors of Bell Pottinger for public affairs work in South Africa commissioned by businesspeople linked to President Zuma was in line with their policy on international trade conducted by British firms.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757278","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-19","<p>The behaviour of Bell Pottinger in South Africa has clearly been completely unacceptable. We welcome the investigations conducted by the Public Relations and Communications Association and Herbert Smith Freehills and the conclusions of their reports.</p><p>At no stage was Her Majesty's Government (HMG) in any way involved in this work, nor consulted in advance.</p><p>The UK has one of the world’s toughest anti-corruption laws, and HMG takes any allegations of bribery or corruption extremely seriously.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","HL1261 ; HL1262","2017-09-19T13:25:13.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757278/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757278/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757278/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-05","Bell Pottinger Group: South Africa","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether Government staff, in the UK or in South Africa, were consulted by Bell Pottinger's Directors before they took income for public affairs work in South Africa commissioned by businesspeople linked to President Zuma.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757279","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-19","<p>The Public Relations and Communication Association (PRCA) has found that Bell Pottinger’s work breached a number of clauses of its Professional Charter, and of its Public Affairs and Lobbying Code of Conduct. The company’s membership of the PRCA has been terminated and it should not be eligible to reapply for corporate membership for a minimum of five years.</p><p>The UK has a world leading system of professional standards and industry specific codes of conduct, which we encourage British companies to uphold in their operations domestically and overseas. Our industry bodies and regulators ensure compliance, as demonstrated by the robust response of the PRCA to Bell Pottinger’s activities in South Africa.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg",,"2017-09-19T12:52:30.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757279/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757279/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757279/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-09-05","Bell Pottinger Group: South Africa","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, in the light of the finding that Bell Pottinger was in breach of the UK Public Relations and Communications Association code of conduct regarding its recent activities in South Africa, what assessment they have made of the extent to which the actions which led to that breach were in contravention of UK trade policy.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757280","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The UK High Commission in South Africa were not involved in this work, nor were they consulted in advance. There was no contact between UK High Commission staff in South Africa and Bell Pottinger during the period 2016 to 2017 to date.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL1266","2017-09-14T15:21:03.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757280/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757280/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757280/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-05","South Africa: Bell Pottinger Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether any UK High Commission staff stationed in South Africa (1) assisted, (2) advised, or (3) were in contact at any time with, Bell Pottinger over its activities in South Africa on behalf of President Zuma's business supporters.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757281","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-14","<p>The UK High Commission in South Africa were not involved in this work, nor were they consulted in advance. There was no contact between UK High Commission staff in South Africa and Bell Pottinger during the period 2016 to 2017 to date.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","HL1265","2017-09-14T15:21:03.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757281/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757281/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757281/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-05","South Africa: Bell Pottinger Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what meetings, telephone calls, or formal or informal contacts UK High Commission staff stationed in South Africa had with Bell Pottinger inside or outside that country in 2016 and in 2017 to date.","false","Biography information for Lord Hain",,"Lord Hain","HL1266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757282","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>It is not permitted contractually for private service providers to use the detainee paid work scheme to replace staffing obligations in immigration removal centres.</p><p> </p><p>None of the work undertaken by detainees on a voluntary basis in this scheme is duplicated by staff or employees of either the Home Office or the private service provider and there are no savings or efficiencies realised by the Home Office or private service providers.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-09-18T13:53:12.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757282/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757282/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757282/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Immigrants: Detainees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the response by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 4 July (HL Deb, cols 788–9) and her Written Answer on 31 July (HL668), regarding rates of pay for work undertaken by immigration removal centre detainees, whether any of the work undertaken by those detainees was duplicated by staff or employees of (1) the Home Office, or (2) the Immigration Removal Centre; if so, what were the rates paid to those detainees for that work; and what is their assessment of why no savings or efficiencies have been realised by the Home Office or private service providers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hamwee",,"Baroness Hamwee","HL1267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757283","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>NHS Resolution (NHSR) provides indemnity cover for negligence claims against the NHS in England on behalf of member organisations. NHSR has provided the following information.</p><p> </p><p>The number of clinical claims received from 2012/13 to 2016/17 and payments made on successful cases where 'anticoagulation', ‘Warfarin’ or 'Non-Vitamin K antagonist' is mentioned in the incident details as at 31 August 2017 is shown in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>Where a claim has been settled by way of a Periodical Payment Order the total value of the damages paid will not be realised until the patient dies. The information in the tables only includes payments to date on such cases.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T12:48:17.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757283/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757283/answer","HL1268 attachment.docx","Clinical claims","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757283/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Anticoagulants","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether there have been any cases brought against the NHS during the past five years that have referenced (1) anticoagulation, (2) warfarin, or (3) non-vitamin K antagonist oral anticoagulants; and if so, how many of those cases were successful and what were the damages awarded.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL1268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757284","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>Although the National Stroke Strategy comes to an end in December, NHS England continues to lead an effective programme of work on prevention and treatment.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is improving acute treatment through the centralisation of care in centres that can provide the highest level of care at all times of the day and week. Stroke is one of the five conditions chosen to deliver the urgent and emergency care standards by this autumn.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has established a cardiovascular disease (CVD) collaborative to bring together relevant stakeholders in the field of CVD and provide a forum where relevant work being undertaken in this area and potential new initiatives can be discussed and responsibilities for action determined.</p><p> </p><p>CVD prevention is a key theme in NHS England’s <em>Five Year Forward View</em> and its NHS RightCare programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England have also recently announced that it will be commissioning the new treatment of thrombectomy (extracting the blood clot causing the blockage to blood flow through a catheter inserted into the artery). This will initially be provided in the neuroscience centres, but in due course additional centres may need to provide this treatment to ensure complete population coverage.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:43:11.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757284/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757284/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757284/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Strokes","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have to ensure progress in the treatment of stroke throughout the country once the National Stroke Strategy comes to an end in December.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL1269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757285","Department of Health","false","2017-09-15","<p>Although the National Stroke Strategy comes to an end in December, NHS England continues to lead an effective programme of work on prevention and treatment.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is improving acute treatment through the centralisation of care in centres that can provide the highest level of care at all times of the day and week. Stroke is one of the five conditions chosen to deliver the urgent and emergency care standards by this autumn.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has established a cardiovascular disease (CVD) collaborative to bring together relevant stakeholders in the field of CVD and provide a forum where relevant work being undertaken in this area and potential new initiatives can be discussed and responsibilities for action determined.</p><p> </p><p>CVD prevention is a key theme in NHS England’s <em>Five Year Forward View</em> and its NHS RightCare programme.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England have also recently announced that it will be commissioning the new treatment of thrombectomy (extracting the blood clot causing the blockage to blood flow through a catheter inserted into the artery). This will initially be provided in the neuroscience centres, but in due course additional centres may need to provide this treatment to ensure complete population coverage.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-15T11:15:17.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757285/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757285/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757285/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Strokes","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have to ensure that new treatments for stroke, including mechanical clot retrieval, will be available throughout the country once the National Stroke Strategy comes to an end in December.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL1270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757286","Department of Health","false","2017-09-14","<p>NHS Digital has advised that it is working towards implementing all the recommendations in Sir Nick Partridge’s <em>Review of Data Releases by the NHS Information Centre</em>. The majority have already been implemented in full and NHS Digital expects the remaining aspects of the one outstanding recommendation to have been implemented by the end of the year.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-09-14T13:58:48.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757286/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757286/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757286/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","NHS: Data Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they intend to implement all the recommendations contained in the report Review of data releases made by the NHS Information Centre led by Sir Nick Partridge in 2014; and if so, how many recommendations remain to be implemented.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757287","Department of Health","false","2017-09-19","<p>Blood plasma supplied by NHS Blood and Transplant for transfusion to hospitals in England is either imported from Austria or comes from United Kingdom donors. Both sources are public, not privately sourced.</p><p>Blood plasma derived medicinal products are subject to medicinal regulation to assure their safety. Data are not held on the number of National Health Service patients receiving blood plasma medicinal products which may have been derived from United States donors.</p><p>The companies that supply plasma derived products to hospitals in England via NHS England’s Commercial Medicines Unit (CMU) frameworks are:</p><p> </p><p>- CSL Behring;</p><p>- Grifols;</p><p>- Octapharma;</p><p>- BPL (Bio Products Laboratory);</p><p>- LFB Biomedicaments;</p><p>- Baxalta (now part of Shire); and</p><p>- Shire Pharmaceuticals.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information is not held on supply of plasma derived medicinal products to NHS trusts outside of a CMU framework agreement.</p><p> </p><p>There are a number of measures in place to ensure the safety and supply of plasma and medicinal products for patients.</p><p> </p><p>All companies wishing to supply plasma derived medicinal products to hospitals in the UK have to be licensed by the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA). There are a series of stringent safety measures in place to prevent infections resulting from the use of medicinal products prepared from human blood or plasma, including selection of donors, screening of individual donations and plasma pools for specific markers of infection and the inclusion of effective manufacturing steps for the inactivation/removal of viruses. These measures are described in detail in the European Medicines Agency’s <em>Guideline on plasma-derived medicinal products</em>. A copy is attached.</p><p> </p><p>The Department works closely with the MHRA, the pharmaceutical industry, NHS England and others to manage risks to the supply chain of blood plasma products to NHS patients.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL1273 ; HL1274 ; HL1275","2017-09-19T15:21:29.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757287/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757287/answer","Guideline on plasma-derived medicinal products.pdf","Guideline on plasma-derived medicinal products","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757287/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Blood Transfusions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many NHS patients (1) are receiving, or (2) have in the last year received, blood plasma from compensated US donors.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL1272"
