"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757453","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The aim of the Neonatal Critical Care Transformation Programme Review is to make recommendations that will support the delivery of high quality, safe, sustainable and equitable models of neonatal care across England. It will be presenting a draft review report to NHS England in October 2017. The draft report will then be consulted upon before being finalised. The Neonatal Critical Care Review has already set out a range of themes that are to be factored into Local Maternity Systems’ Transformation Plans.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:33:04.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757453/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757453/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757453/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Neonatal Critical Care Transformation Programme Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the key milestones are of the Neonatal Transformation Review; and when that review plans to (a) announce its plans, (b) consult and (c) report its findings.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","8583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757454","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The information is not available in the format requested. NHS England publishes trust-level data on the number of attendances at accident and emergency (A&amp;E) departments, but data on attendances at individual hospital sites are not available. The table below provides the number of A&amp;E attendances at Calderdale and Huddersfield NHS Foundation Trust for the full years 2010-11 to 2016-17 and the year to date position in 2017-18.</p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Attendances at A&amp;E</p></td><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18 Year to Date*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>134,528</p></td><td><p>137,821</p></td><td><p>140,825</p></td><td><p>138,799</p></td><td><p>142,038</p></td><td><p>148,355</p></td><td><p>151,354</p></td><td><p>51,194</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*Activity from April to July 2017 inclusive</p><p>Sources: NHS England:</p><p>2010 data is from the Quarterly Monitoring of Accident and Emergency (QMAE) collection. The number of emergency admissions not via A&amp;E were not collected on the QMAE return.</p><p>2011-12 to June 2015 data is from the A&amp;E Attendance and Emergency Admissions Weekly Sitrep collection.</p><p>From July 2015 data comes from the A&amp;E Attendance and Emergency Admissions Monthly Sitrep collection.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:37:13.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757454/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757454/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757454/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Huddersfield Royal Infirmary: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients were admitted to the Huddersfield Royal Infirmary Accident and Emergency Department in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","8656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757455","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>It is for individual National Health Service trusts and foundation trusts to make decisions in consultation with local stakeholders (e.g. clinical commissioning groups) about their facilities and accordingly they are responsible for developing their own business cases for major new investment projects. They are required to do so with regard to value for money and affordability of the different options. The Department and NHS Improvement works closely with trusts going through this process. HM Treasury are responsible for the policy on the use of Private Finance 2 (PF2), the successor to the Private Finance Initiative, introduced under the Coalition Government in 2012. This introduced changes to the previous model.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:10:44.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757455/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757455/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Hospitals: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what his policy is on the use of private financial investment companies to fund the building of new hospitals.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","8657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757456","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:55:12.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757456/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757456/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757456/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Ambulance Services: Lost Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times items belonging to patients using ambulance services in England and Wales were lost in the most recent annual data period.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","8652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757457","Department of Health","false","2017-09-12","<p>This Government does not recognise so-called ‘gay conversion therapy’ as a legitimate treatment. A person's sexual orientation is not an illness to be cured. We have already worked with the main registration and accreditation bodies for psychotherapy and counselling practitioners, including the UK Council for Psychotherapy, to develop a Memorandum of Understanding to put a stop to this practice.</p><p>We are not aware of widespread instances of gay conversion therapy happening in the United Kingdom, but we want to get a better idea of the extent to which it is being practised. That is why we included questions on this topic in our national LGBT survey, which was launched this summer. We will publish the survey results and our response in the new year.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-09-12T14:37:15.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757457/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757457/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Gay Conversion Therapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will proscribe the practice of conversion therapy in England.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","8646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757458","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:56:42.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757458/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757458/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757458/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Surgical Mesh Implants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on ongoing or long-term delays for women seeking to have vaginal meshes removed.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757459","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Transvaginal meshes are used to treat women suffering from stress urinary incontinence or pelvic organ prolapse.</p><p> </p><p>The Department and NHS England have not had any discussions with hospital trusts regarding the use of the vaginal meshes to treat urinary tract infections.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-13T10:53:47.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757459/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757459/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757459/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Urinary Tract Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with hospital trusts on the use of vaginal meshes to treat urinary tract infections.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757460","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Public Health England (PHE) reports data for reference laboratory confirmed cases of Lyme disease in England and Wales. Collated United Kingdom-wide data is available up to 2015 and can be found in the PHE annual Zoonoses reports, available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/zoonoses-uk-annual-reports" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/zoonoses-uk-annual-reports</a></p><p> </p><p>Provisional figures for 2016 and 2017 can be found in the 2016 end of year (Q1 – Q4) Health Protection Report links below:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/593004/hpr0617_zoos.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/593004/hpr0617_zoos.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The 2017 Q1-Q2 Health Protection Report can be accessed via:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/637401/hpr2817_zoos.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/637401/hpr2817_zoos.pdf</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:31:44.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757460/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757460/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757460/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Lyme Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been given a diagnosis of Lyme disease in the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757461","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>For the year 2016 under the offence of ‘care provider ill treatment/wilful neglect of an individual or breach of duty of care’, 17 had cautions issued, two were fined, 72 were proceeded against and 25 were convicted.</p><p> </p><p>The official statistics provided by the Ministry of Justice do not distinguish between National Health Service and private care homes, nor do they categorise offences by reference to ‘sanctions’.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-09-13T15:50:36.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757461/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757461/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757461/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Care Homes: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many (a) NHS and (b) private care homes have been sanctioned for cases of neglect in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757462","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Many of the key commitments in our world-leading childhood obesity plan, launched in August 2016, will have an impact on tackling obesity across all age groups. These include the soft drinks industry levy and sugar reduction programme, which will reduce the amount of sugar we all consume. Alongside this, Public Health England is now considering the evidence on children’s calorie consumption and will set the ambition for a calorie reduction programme to remove excess calories from the foods children consume the most.</p><p> </p><p>Steps to tackle obesity in adults include the NHS Diabetes Prevention Programme, which identifies those at high risk of developing diabetes and provides tailored, personalised help to reduce that risk including education on healthy eating and lifestyle and bespoke physical exercise programmes to tackle excess weight. There is also Public Health England’s “One You” marketing campaign, which engages adults in healthier behaviours including better eating habits and increasing physical activity.</p><p> </p><p>A copy of “Childhood Obesity: A Plan for Action” is attached and is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/546588/Childhood_obesity_2016__2__acc.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/546588/Childhood_obesity_2016__2__acc.pdf</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T15:08:13.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757462/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757462/answer","PQ8484 attached document.pdf","PQ8484 attached document","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757462/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to reduce deaths due to obesity.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757463","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has published technology appraisal guidance recommending Zytiga (abiraterone) for the treatment of metastatic prostate cancer subject to a commercial access arrangement agreed between the manufacturer and NHS England.</p><p> </p><p>National Health Service commissioners in England are legally required to fund drugs and treatments recommended in NICE technology appraisal guidance. This is reflected in the NHS Constitution as a right to NICE approved drugs.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:30:44.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757463/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757463/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757463/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Abiraterone","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will make Zytiga available on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757464","Department of Health","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government is undertaking a range of measures to ensure sufficient nursing workforce supply:</p><p> </p><p>On 1 August 2017 the Government changed the funding system for pre-registration nurse training from National Health Service-funded tuition and bursaries to the standard student support system. This change means we have moved away from centrally imposed number controls and financial limitations and therefore the artificial cap has been removed. We expect that these reforms will be enable universities to offer up to an additional 10,000 training places by 2020, for nurses, midwives and allied health profession students.</p><p> </p><p>Developing new routes into nursing is a priority for the Department. In November 2016 the new Nursing Associate role and the Nursing Degree Apprenticeship was announced. Once established, up to 1,000 apprentice nurses could join the NHS each year. In addition the Department is working with its arm’s length bodies to ensure that the NHS retains more of its existing workforce and invests in the Return to Nursing Practice Programme.</p><p> </p><p>Agenda for Change - the national pay system under which nurses are paid - includes mechanisms that enable trusts to target pay to address local recruitment and retention issues. In making recommendations to the Government on pay for nurses and other staff covered by Agenda for Change, the independent NHS Pay Review Body considers evidence from a wide range of stakeholders including trades unions, NHS Employers, NHS Providers, NHS England, NHS Improvement, Health Education England and others, not just from the Government. In its March 2017 report the NHS Pay Review Body noted that it had received no evidence from any party, including trades unions, for making any changes to the existing mechanisms; and that there was no support from any party for targeting the pay award for 2017/18.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","7317","2017-09-12T14:13:48.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757464/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757464/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757464/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Nurses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to address nurse shortages and pay gaps between English regions.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757465","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Data on the number of people diagnosed with chronic stomach pains is not collected.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:25:10.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757465/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757465/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757465/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Gastrointestinal System: Pain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people in the UK have been diagnosed with chronic stomach pains in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757466","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:24:15.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757466/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757466/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757466/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Menometrorrhagia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many women have been diagnosed with menometrorrhagia in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757467","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T15:06:38.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757467/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757467/answer","PQ 8491 Final Response.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ8491","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757467/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Thyroid Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people in UK have been diagnosed with thyroid cancer in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757468","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>NHS England is committed to providing timely access to new drugs and medical technologies and is working closely with the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence on how this can be best achieved, while also ensuring the financial sustainability of the National Health Service. Clinical commissioning groups are also responsible for working with their local communities to understand the needs of the local populations and make decisions about how best to commission services that meet those needs.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:26:08.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757468/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757468/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757468/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Heart and Kidney Diseases: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to increase the availability of treatments to reduce heart and kidney disease.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757469","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>Trastuzumab emtansine (Kadcyla) has been funded and available to National Health Service patients in England since 2013 for the treatment of patients with HER2-positive unresectable, locally advanced or metastatic breast cancer after trastuzumab and a taxane.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:28:43.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757469/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757469/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757469/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Trastuzumab Emtansine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to make Kadcyla available to patients in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757470","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>No specific discussions have taken place between my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health and the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport on this issue. Officials across Government departments work closely together to tackle the harms that all illicit drugs cause, including those used illegally in sports to improve performance.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:16:21.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757470/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757470/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757470/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Drugs: Sports Competitors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport on steps to reduce illegal drug-taking in sports.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757472","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested is not held centrally. The Home Office holds information on notifiable offences recorded by the police including theft offences, but it is not possible to tell from this information how many dogs or pets in general were stolen.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-12T16:53:20.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757472/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757472/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757472/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Theft: Dogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many dogs have been reported stolen in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757473","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>In its manifesto the Government has set out the intention to extend the use of the First Past the Post system to Police and Crime Commission and mayoral elections, replacing the currently used Supplementary Vote system.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T12:03:40.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757473/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757473/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757473/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Police and Crime Commissioners: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether it is his policy to change the electoral system for police and crime commissioner elections.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757474","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The number of armed response vehicles (ARVs) by force is not centrally recorded. It is for Chief Officers in England and Wales to make decisions about the deployment of ARVs, based on a thorough assessment of the threat and risk in their local area.</p><p>From April 2016, as part of our £144m Armed Police Uplift Programme, the total number of ARVs across England and Wales has increased by 41, with an additional 650 ARV Officers. The second phase of the programme, on track to deliver next year, will see an uplift of highly specialist counter-terrorism firearms officers, increasing the total number of armed officers by around 1,000 by the end of 2018.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-12T16:54:47.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757474/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757474/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757474/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police: Armed Response Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many armed response vehicles each police force had in each year from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757475","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-13","<p>On 18 January the previous government announced that it would set out a strategy for victims of crime within 12 months, and that it would take the appropriate action to give effect to the strategy, including bringing forward any appropriate legislation.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-09-13T15:19:08.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757475/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757475/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757475/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-05","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans he has to bring forward legislation on victims' rights to make clear what level of service they should expect from the police.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757476","Department of Health","false","2017-09-13","<p>At present a local authority has the ability to appoint a police and crime commissioner to its health and wellbeing board (HWB), although it is not mandatory.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently considering the role and membership of HWBs, both voluntary and prescribed.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-13T16:27:57.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757476/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757476/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757476/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-05","Police and Crime Commissioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to ensure police and crime commissioners sit on local health and wellbeing boards.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757477","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>Core grant funding for policing is provided to Police and Crime Commissioners or equivalent local policing bodies on an un-ringfenced basis. Under the measures set out in the Police Reform and Social Responsibility Act 2011, PCCs are required to set budgets and determine local precept levels.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-13T16:08:49.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757477/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757477/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757477/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police and Crime Commissioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she plans to devolve budget responsibility to local police and crime commissioners.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","8507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757478","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Home Office collects data on the number of anti-social behaviour incidents recorded by the police forces in England Wales. It is not possible to tell from these data how many incidents related to vehicles or the type of vehicle involved.</p><p>Anti-social behaviour incidents recorded by the police are published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) and can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesbulletintables" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesbulletintables</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-12T16:49:12.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757478/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757478/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757478/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Motorcycles: Antisocial Behaviour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many reports of anti-social behaviour in connection with mopeds were made in Hornsey and Wood Green constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757479","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The 2015 Spending Review protected overall police spending in real terms. Since 2015/16 police forces have received broadly flat cash budgets and we are increasing investment in transformation, improved communications and technology capabilities.</p><p> </p><p>The Mayor for London wrote to the Home Secretary in July to state that he had opened a consultation on the potential closure of front counters to reduce costs.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the most effective use of the Metropolitan Police’s resources, including the number and operating hours of police stations, are for Chief Officers and the Mayor’s Office for Policing and Crime (MOPAC) who are held to account by the communities they serve.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","8520 ; 8522","2017-09-13T15:45:19.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757479/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757479/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757479/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police Stations: Hornsey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent discussions she has had with (a) the Mayor of London and (b) Mayor Sophie Linden on the current and future operation of Hornsey police station.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757480","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The 2015 Spending Review protected overall police spending in real terms. Since 2015/16 police forces have received broadly flat cash budgets and we are increasing investment in transformation, improved communications and technology capabilities.</p><p> </p><p>The Mayor for London wrote to the Home Secretary in July to state that he had opened a consultation on the potential closure of front counters to reduce costs.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the most effective use of the Metropolitan Police’s resources, including the number and operating hours of police stations, are for Chief Officers and the Mayor’s Office for Policing and Crime (MOPAC) who are held to account by the communities they serve.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","8522 ; 8524","2017-09-13T15:45:19.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757480/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757480/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757480/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police Stations: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what impact assessment her Department has made of plans to close half of London's police stations.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8520"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757481","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>The information requested is not held by the Home Office. Anti-social behaviour is not a substantive offence in law therefore it is not possible to be convicted for anti-social behaviour. Furthermore, convictions data are the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice.</p><p> </p><p>Anti-social behaviour incidents recorded by the police are published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) and can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesbulletintables" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/crimeandjustice/datasets/crimeinenglandandwalesbulletintables</a></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-20T13:20:21.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757481/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757481/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757481/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Motorcycles: Antisocial Behaviour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the rate of conviction for anti-social behaviour related to moped use was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757482","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The 2015 Spending Review protected overall police spending in real terms. Since 2015/16 police forces have received broadly flat cash budgets and we are increasing investment in transformation, improved communications and technology capabilities.</p><p> </p><p>The Mayor for London wrote to the Home Secretary in July to state that he had opened a consultation on the potential closure of front counters to reduce costs.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the most effective use of the Metropolitan Police’s resources, including the number and operating hours of police stations, are for Chief Officers and the Mayor’s Office for Policing and Crime (MOPAC) who are held to account by the communities they serve.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","8520 ; 8524","2017-09-13T15:45:19.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757482/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757482/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757482/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police Stations: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received from the Metropolitan Police on proposed closures of police stations.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","8522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757483","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>We are confident that a future partnership between the UK and EU is in the interests of both sides, so we are approaching the exit negotiations anticipating success. We do not want or expect a no deal outcome.</p><p>However, a responsible government should prepare for all potential outcomes, including the unlikely scenario in which no mutually satisfactory agreement can be reached. This is exactly what we are doing across the whole of Government.</p><p>The Home Office leads on EU Exit planning across a number of justice and home affairs areas, including Immigration and Security and Law Enforcement cooperation. Home Office EU Exit contingency preparations are well underway and will continue as an ongoing process until the EU Exit negotiations are complete.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-13T16:07:57.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757483/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757483/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757483/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Emergencies: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what contingency planning has been conducted by her Department in the event that no deal is reached on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","8582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757484","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>Tackling knife crime is a priority for the Government and we are taking action. Our approach is centred on four key strands – early intervention and prevention, working with the police on operations and enforcement, work with retailers on responsible sales and work on the legislative framework. As part of this wide approach, on 18 July the Government announced its intention to consult on a number of proposals to tackle knife crime . The consultation respond to concerns about how some retailers are selling knives online. We will use the responses to the consultation to inform further work to assess the impact on these proposals.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-09-13T16:07:08.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757484/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757484/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757484/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Knives: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the effect on small online businesses of proposed changes to the online sale of knives.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","8658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757485","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government has protected overall police spending in real terms since the Spending Review in 2015. In addition, nine police forces have submitted a total of 11 bids collectively, for Home Office innovation or transformation funding in relation to local projects involving support for people affected by mental health issues. Of these, six of the bids have been successful.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-12T16:55:54.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757485/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757485/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police forces have made representations for additional funding to support people affected with mental health issues.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","8659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757486","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>Many police forces have local joint initiatives with health partners to respond to people with mental health issues. For example, approximately 38 police forces in England have access to a Street Triage service – where mental health professionals accompany police officers on patrol and all forces have access to mental health partners who provide advice and support them in dealing with the public. Information on the average number of responses to calls from people with a mental health issue, by the police, is an operational matter for individual police forces and is not held centrally by the Home Office.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-09-12T10:53:46.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757486/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757486/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757486/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Police: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average number of police responses to calls from people with a mental health issue was in (a) England and (b) West Yorkshire in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","8660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757487","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>This data could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-13T15:51:12.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757487/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757487/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757487/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Immigration Controls: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been (a) detained and (b) deported in each year since 2010 as a result of information received from hon. Members via her Department's immigration enforcement hotlines and webpages.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","8563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757488","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>Since records began MPs have submitted information to the Home Office online on 85 occasions - 2014 (4), 2015 (44), 2016 (29) and in 2017 (8). The have contacted us by telephone on 13 times – 2013 (4), 2014 (2), 2015 (5) and in 2017 (2).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-13T15:52:05.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757488/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757488/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Immigration Controls: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many communications were received from hon. Members to her Department on immigration enforcement hotlines and webpages in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","8566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757489","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Government has no plans to introduce a fixed time limit on immigration detention as this would only encourage detainees to refuse to cooperate with immigration and asylum processes until they reached the point at which they had to be released from detention. Published Home Office policy is clear, however, that detention is only used for the shortest period necessary.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-13T15:55:16.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757489/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757489/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if her Department will introduce a time limit for holding immigration and asylum applicants.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757490","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>The data passed by Members of Parliament to the Home Office does not contravene the Data Protection Act 1998 as information is passed with the consent of the constituent.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-13T15:52:48.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757490/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757490/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Immigration Controls: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether immigration enforcement information passed to her Department by hon. Members contravenes the Data Protection Act 1998.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","8552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757491","Home Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>A future partnership between the UK and EU on security and law enforcement issues is in the interests of both sides and we approach negotiations anticipating success. We do not want or expect a no deal outcome. However, a responsible government should prepare for all potential outcomes. That is exactly what we are doing across the whole of Government.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office leads on EU Exit planning across a number of justice and home affairs areas, including Immigration and Security and Law Enforcement cooperation. Home Office EU Exit contingency planning is well underway, and this will continue as an ongoing process until the EU Exit negotiations are complete.</p><p> </p><p>In relation to national security, Article 4(2) of the Treaty on European Union sets out that national security remains the sole responsibility of Member States rather than the European Union.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-09-13T15:20:55.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757491/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757491/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","National Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what contingency planning has been conducted by her Department on matters of national security in the event that no deal is reached on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","8579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757492","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p>Published data on unaccompanied asylum seeking children can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/how-many-people-do-we-grant-asylum-or-protection-to#unaccompanied-asylum-seeking-children" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/how-many-people-do-we-grant-asylum-or-protection-to#unaccompanied-asylum-seeking-children</a>.</p><p> </p><p>There are over 4,000 unaccompanied asylum seeking children (UASC) in local authority care in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The National Transfer Scheme was launched on 1 July 2016 and has been working to ensure a fairer allocation of UASC across the UK. A significant number of local authorities have participated in the scheme and enabled the transfer of children away from local authorities with a disproportionate number of UASC in their care.</p><p> </p><p>The Government welcomes all offers from local authorities with capacity to look after UASC. We continue to engage with local authorities across the country to encourage further participation.</p><p> </p><p>In support of the National Transfer Scheme central government increased funding to local authorities caring for UASC by up to 33% in July 2016. In August 2017 a review of funding for UASC was launched and all local authorities who currently look after unaccompanied children have been invited to submit evidence.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-04T13:46:02.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757492/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757492/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757492/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many unaccompanied children are supported by each local authority; how many children each local authority has offered to support; and what support has been offered to local authorities to increase their capacity to provide appropriate psychological support for unaccompanied child refugees.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","8593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757493","Home Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The responsibility for maintaining law and order in France lies with the French government.</p><p> </p><p>No one should live in makeshift camps in Calais, which is why we continue to work closely with the French authorities on border security and migration issues, including helping to fund alternative facilities elsewhere in France for Calais migrants provided by the French government. However, the primary responsibility for unaccompanied children lies with the authorities in the country in which children are present. The UK government does not have the authority to operate unauthorised on the territory of another sovereign state.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is also proud to have transferred over 750 children from France to the UK last year as a result of the Calais camp clearance, and we continue to work with the French authorities to transfer unaccompanied children who may be eligible under the Dublin Regulation or section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-12T09:47:17.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757493/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757493/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-05","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking together with the French Government to reduce the level of unnecessary force used by the police in that country against child refugees and to ensure the protection of unaccompanied child refugees seeking a place of safety in the UK.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","8592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757494","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Global Learning Programme comes to an end in July 2018. We are currently consulting on potential future work on development education, with a focus on increasing impact and better engaging UK citizens in tackling poverty and achieving the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:51:43.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757494/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757494/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757494/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Global Learning Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans she has for the future of the Global Learning programme.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","8649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757495","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>There will be no decisions on future UK/EU policy until the Government’s negotiations on exiting the EU have concluded.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:52:13.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757495/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757495/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757495/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Development Education and Awareness Raising Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether it is her policy that the UK should continue to participate in the Europe Aid Development Awareness programme after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","8650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757496","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>DFID remains committed to development education in the UK. We are currently consulting on potential future work on development education, with a focus on increasing impact and better engaging UK citizens in tackling poverty and achieving the Sustainable Development Goals.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:52:37.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757496/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757496/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757496/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Development Aid: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans she has for the future of development awareness education.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","8651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757497","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Department for International Development (DFID) is providing assistance to refugees and migrants at risk of trafficking and exploitation in Libya. So far this year, DFID has supported more than 20,000 emergency interventions such as healthcare, psychosocial support, hygiene kits and safe shelter. The UK Government is also assisting vulnerable migrants with voluntary returns from Libya – so far our support has helped more than 1,200 individuals to return home.</p><p>The UK government continues to support the Libyan authorities to tackle smuggling and organised immigration crime. We also continue to press for refugees and migrants in Libya to be treated in accordance with international norms and standards.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:47:50.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757497/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757497/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757497/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Libya: Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to support the victims of human trafficking and exploitation in Libya.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","8549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757498","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>The UK provides direct financial aid to the Palestinian Authority Ministry of Finance and Planning to contribute to the salaries of vetted public servants. A breakdown of funding by financial years is below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Beneficiary</p></td><td><p>Purpose</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>2016/17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ministry of Finance and Planning</p></td><td><p>For financial years 2012/13 – 2015/16, UK funding contributed to public servants salaries through the EU PEGASE mechanism. In 2016/17 UK funding was specifically earmarked for West Bank health and education public servants salaries.</p></td><td><p>£34.1 million</p></td><td><p>£41.6 million</p></td><td><p>£22 million</p></td><td><p>£24.8 million</p></td><td><p>£25 million</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:49:16.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757498/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757498/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757498/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Palestinians: Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much development funding was provided by her Department to the Palestinian Authority in each of the last five financial years; what organisations were so funded; and what the objectives of that funding were.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","8550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757499","Department for International Development","false","2017-09-12","<p>UK financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority is provided through a European Union mechanism. It pays for vetted West Bank health and education public servants. The EU mechanism uses a pre- and post-verification system which validates that the funds transferred into a dedicated sub-account for UKaid and spent on the salaries of eligible beneficiaries on a vetted list. The PA payroll is checked by independent auditors, and payments made to all eligible beneficiaries are traced through the verification process.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-09-12T09:51:13.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757499/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757499/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757499/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-09-05","Palestinians: Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what safeguards her Department has in place to ensure that international development funding to the Palestinian Authority is not used for the payment of terror salaries or associated purposes.","false","Biography information for Paul Masterton","East Renfrewshire","Paul Masterton","8551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757500","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>Protecting pedestrians and all road users is a key priority. We have some of the safest roads in the world but are always looking at ways to make them safer.</p><p>There are road traffic offences already that apply to cyclists, but the Department is carefully considering the implications of the recent tragic case of Mrs Briggs, who died after a collision with a cyclist, including as to whether current legislation is adequate.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-13T11:03:31.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757500/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757500/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757500/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Road Traffic Act 1988: Cycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if his Department will bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Road Traffic Act 1988 to ensure that cyclists are bound by that legislation.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757501","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-13","<p>All adult prisoners in English prisons have an assessment of their maths and English needs on entry to prison, when they transfer between prisons, and prior to release.</p><p> </p><p>As set out in the White Paper, “Prison Safety and Reform” published in November 2016, we will ensure that a core common curriculum, focused on the underpinning basic skills of maths and English, will apply in every prison and that every prisoner will have a Personal Learning Plan linked to their sentence plan. We have introduced additional assessment of prisoners’ levels of maths and English on transfer between prisons and on release, gathering data that will allow us to compare prisoners’ attainment in maths and English on release with that at the start of custody, and to measure progress made by prisoners whilst serving their sentences.</p><p> </p><p>We have already introduced significant flexibility in our funding rules for prison education, giving prison governors more ability to put in place a curriculum that meets the needs of learners and responds to the demand for skills in the areas to which those prisoners will be released. Once existing prison education contracts end, we will make prison governors fully responsible for education provision in their prisons, commissioning the services they think are most appropriate in their individual prison. This will allow governors to decide how to structure their educational regime, and who delivers it, while following a core common curriculum set nationally which will focus on maths and English.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-09-13T16:56:15.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757501/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757501/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757501/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-05","Prisoners: Basic Skills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department has taken to increase the levels of literacy and numeracy in the prison population.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757502","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-13","<p>We have put in place a range of measures to support prisoners who are at risk of self-harm or suicide, especially in the early period in custody, when they are at their most vulnerable.</p><p>We have established a Prison Safety programme to support establishments in the implementation of the reforms set out in the Prison Safety and Reform White Paper, including our investment in an additional 2,500 staff who will help deliver consistent, purposeful regimes and allow us to introduce a new key worker role to support better staff-prisoner relationships.</p><p>We are rolling out new training across the estate to support our staff to identify the risks and triggers of suicide and self-harm and understand what they can do to support prisoners at risk. We have put in place specialist roles - regional safer custody teams - in every region to provide advice to prisons and to spread good practice on identifying and supporting prisoners at risk. We are using experts, including providing extra funding for the Samaritans, to provide targeted support for prison staff and to prisoners directly.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-09-13T16:56:20.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757502/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757502/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757502/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-05","Prisoners: Self-harm","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department has taken to reduce the incidence of self-harming of people held in the Prison Estate.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757503","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-09-13","<p>UK Anti-Doping issued the following number of sanctions to athletes with Adverse Analytical Findings;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year (1 January to 31 December)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of athletes sanctioned by UKAD following an Adverse Analytical Finding</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017 to date</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>31</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figures refer to the date that the athlete’s sanction was made public, in some cases the date that the athlete provided the positive sample may have been in an earlier year.</p><p>The figures relate to “Presence” cases only (i.e. the athlete provided an Adverse Analytical Finding). ‘Non-Analytical Findings’ (refusing a test, trafficking banned substances etc) are not included in these figures.</p><p> </p><p>UK Anti-Doping is a world leading National Anti-Doping Organisation (NADO) with a strong testing programme, this is evidenced by the World Anti-Doping Agency asking UKAD to manage the testing programme in Russia as part of the work to make the Russian NADO compliant once again with the World Ant-Doping Code.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is fully committed to eradicating the use of performance enhancing substances and methods in sport. Performance enhancing drugs remain a threat to the integrity of sport and the health and wellbeing of all our athletes.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-09-13T14:49:27.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757503/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757503/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757503/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-09-05","Drugs: Sports Competitors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many people have been found guilty of illegal drug-taking in sport in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757504","Prime Minister","false","2017-09-13","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the press release issued on 5 September following my phone call with President Trump and which is available on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-call-with-president-trump-5-september-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-call-with-president-trump-5-september-2017</a></p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-09-13T12:52:36.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757504/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757504/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757504/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-09-05","North Korea: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will make it her policy to urge the President of the US to engage in high-level dialogue without pre-conditions with North Korea on preserving peace and security; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","8500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757505","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>​The United States is one of our closest allies and a Presidential visit is an opportunity to further advance that important relationship. It remains in the UK's public interest to work closely with the US on a range of foreign, security and trade policy issues.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-09-12T15:10:37.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757505/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757505/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757505/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-09-05","State Visits: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what benefits he anticipates will accrue to the British public from President Trump's forthcoming official visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","8647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757506","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>Tolls for bridges, tunnels and roads operated by public authorities are outside the scope of VAT. As a result, no VAT is charged on the Mersey Tunnel tolls and it will not be charged on tolls for the Mersey Gateway.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-11T09:37:02.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757506/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757506/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757506/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","River Mersey: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether VAT is levied on Mersey (a) tunnel and (b) bridge charges.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","8595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757507","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Department’s assessment of the business case for the Crossing, which included a consideration of the overall effects of tolling levels on road users, showed that the new Crossing will reduce congestion and improve journey times for users. Tolling levels for the new Mersey Gateway Crossing are the responsibility of Halton Borough Council. Any assessment of the local impact of these tolls is therefore a matter for the Council rather than this Department.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-09-11T09:42:11.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757507/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757507/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757507/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Mersey Gateway Bridge: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect on the (a) local economy and (b) economy of the North West region of new Mersey crossing tolls.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","8594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757508","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>Officials continue to work with Govia Thameslink Railway (GTR) on implementing part time season tickets and are currently discussing the enhancements to GTR’s KeyGo product that would be required to run a trial. The routes and timescale on which any trial may take place will be agreed after those enhancements have been delivered.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-12T14:18:32.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757508/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757508/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757508/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Govia Thameslink Railway: Season Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for season tickets for part-time workers to be introduced on the Govia Thameslink Railway franchise; and what the reasons are for the time taken to implement such tickets.","true","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","8498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757509","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-12","<p>We are currently working with Rail North and Network Rail to develop very significant improvements for rail passengers on the route from 2022. These could be the result of investment in new trains, electrification or other infrastructure work. The options will be costed by December, ahead of a decision next year.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-09-12T12:07:16.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757509/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757509/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Roads: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on the trans-Pennine upgrade programme; and what the timetable is for completion.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","8496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757510","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-13","<p>Payments of Housing Benefit can be made to either the landlord or the claimant. We recognise that in a minority of cases some claimants may not utilise their Housing Benefit for the purposes of paying their rent. To minimise this we have put safeguards in place to pay Housing Benefit directly to the landlord if the claimant is likely to have difficulty in managing their rent payments, or is unlikely to pay their rent or is in rent arrears equivalent to eight weeks.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-13T13:16:52.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757510/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757510/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757510/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-05","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what safeguards his Department has introduced to ensure that when housing benefit is paid to tenants it is paid to the landlord.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757511","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-13","<p>The IT that is currently used to administer Access to Work (AtW) is not configured to issue monthly statements. We are continuing to develop the AtW digital service and we are testing new features and improvements with users as part of this process.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-09-13T13:50:45.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757511/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757511/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757511/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-05","Access to Work Programme: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, for what reasons people receiving Access to Work grants do not receive a monthly statement setting out the amount of their remaining allowance.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","8477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757512","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>In the first 6 months of 2017 the CMS has received 25 complaints where the 25% payment reassessment threshold was recorded to be part of, but not necessarily the main driver of, the complaint.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T11:36:55.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757512/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757512/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757512/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-05","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints the Child Maintenance Service received in the first six months of 2017 on the 25 per cent threshold for payment reassessment.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","8587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757513","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-09-11","<p>Forecasts of Housing Benefit expenditure, consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s March 2017 Economic and Fiscal Outlook are available on gov.uk at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2017</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Expenditure on Housing Benefit for households living in the private rented sector in 2017/18 is forecast to be £8.8 billion. This includes the Housing Benefit that would have been paid to households who are instead receiving housing support through Universal Credit.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-09-11T14:27:22.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757513/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757513/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757513/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-09-05","Housing Benefit: Private Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the total sum of housing benefit payable to households living in the private rented sector in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","8560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757514","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>We are currently working on our ambitious and robust Clean Growth Strategy, which will include proposals for reducing carbon emissions for a wide-range of sectors, including homes. It will be published shortly.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-09-11T16:43:09.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757514/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757514/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757514/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-05","Carbon Emissions: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Government's Clean Growth Plan will include measures to reduce carbon emissions from homes.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","8648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757515","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-12","<p>Ofcom is the independent regulator with responsibility for postal services, including courier companies.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-12T15:00:46.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757515/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757515/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-05","Courier Services: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department takes to regulate and monitor courier companies in the UK.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","8468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757516","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-09-11","<p>Since 2011, the number of women on FTSE 350 boards has more than doubled from 289 (9.5% of positions) to 744 (24.4%). There are now only 7 all-male boards, down from 152 in 2011.</p><p> </p><p>We are going further and are supporting the work of the business-led Hampton-Alexander Review and its target of 33% women on FTSE 350 boards by 2020.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-09-11T12:48:58.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757516/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757516/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757516/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-09-05","Directors: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what progress has been made on increasing the representation of women on company boards.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","8534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757517","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-13","<p>We have released information on the UK's senior negotiating team on<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/620076/Biographies_of_the_Civil_Service_representatives_for_the_negotiations_with_the_EU_.pdf" target="_blank"> Gov.uk</a>. As an indication of the number of civil servants in attendance at negotiations in Brussels, at the second round we had over 90 civil servants in attendance, and for the third round, over 100. The total number of staff will vary from round to round as we deploy the negotiating team best able to work on the issues under negotiation. We are drawing together expertise from a wide range of departments where there is specific relevant knowledge on the issues to be negotiated.</p><p>I can confirm that of the Department for Exiting the European Union staff who attended the negotiations in July and August, none were seconded from outside of Government. We do not hold information on the contractual arrangements of individuals from other Government Departments.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-09-13T11:41:26.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757517/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757517/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757517/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-05","Civil Servants: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many civil servants have been sent to Brussels at any point to engage in the detail of the Brexit negotiation talks; and how many of these have been seconded from outside the Government.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757518","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-13","<p>It is not standard practice to provide an ongoing commentary on internal analytical work that is being carried out within government. The Government's plan for leaving the EU has been discussed at length, and Parliament will have a say on the final deal we achieve with the European Union by putting that deal to a vote in both Houses before it comes into force. But as Parliament has also agreed, we will not publish anything that would undermine our ability to negotiate the best deal for the UK.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-09-13T11:38:36.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757518/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757518/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-05","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what plans his Department has to publish studies into the effect of the UK leaving the EU on different sectors of the UK economy.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","8561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757519","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-09-11","<p>We have discussed EU social security coordination rules with the EU during the July and August negotiation rounds. The progress of these discussions has been set out in the published joint comparison table. It can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/641334/2017-08-30_-_EU_UK_Comparison_Table_CR_AUGUST_day_2_FINAL_AGREED_VERSION_AGREED_with_Cion_V2.2.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/641334/2017-08-30_-_EU_UK_Comparison_Table_CR_AUGUST_day_2_FINAL_AGREED_VERSION_AGREED_with_Cion_V2.2.pdf</a></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-09-11T17:01:50.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757519/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757519/answer","2017-08-30_-_EU_UK_Comparison_Table_CR_AUGUST_day_2_FINAL_AGREED_VERSION_AGREED_with_Cion_V2.2.pdf","August joint comparison table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757519/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-09-05","Social Security Benefits: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many times his Department raised the issue of the co-ordination of social security entitlements for people moving within the EU during the negotiations on the UK leaving the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","8588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757520","Attorney General","false","2017-09-15","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (‘CPS’) conducts extradition proceedings on behalf of foreign states in compliance with section 190 of the Extradition Act 2003.</p><p> </p><p>The CPS’ costs for the first extradition proceedings from 2006-2009 was £348,029.29. No costs were incurred in the period 2009-2013. In respect of the second extradition proceedings, the costs incurred from 2013 to date of writing are £291.277.88, although some further costs are anticipated. The total costs to date are £639,307.17. CPS records do not capture the cost of internal time spent by CPS staff on individual cases.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-09-15T18:12:10.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757520/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757520/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-09-05","Extradition: Rwanda","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what cost has been incurred by the Crown Prosecution Service in each of the last 11 years of extradition proceedings in relation to suspected Rwandan genocide by Dr Vincent Bajinya, Charles Munyaneza, Emmanuel Nteziryayo, Celestin Ugirashebuja and Celestin Mutabaruka.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Mitchell","Sutton Coldfield","Mr Andrew Mitchell","8675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757521","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-09-12","<p>The government published an action plan in July to tackle the use of acid and other corrosives in violent attacks. The action plan will ensure legislation covering the use of acid and other corrosives in attacks is fit for purpose, that it is understood and consistently applied.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-09-12T13:18:49.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757521/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757521/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757521/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-09-05","Crimes of Violence: Acids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what progress the Government has made on plans to strengthen sentencing powers for acid attacks.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","8876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757522","Attorney General","false","2017-09-18","<p>The Law Officers have had no recent discussions with social media providers on users’ postings and the provisions of the Contempt of Court Act 1981. The Attorney General has, however, announced on 15 September 2017 a Call for Evidence to consider the impact of social media on the administration of justice. The Call for Evidence will assess the risks arising from social media to the fairness of criminal trials including contempt of court, the right to anonymity of victims and the integrity of judicial orders in criminal proceedings.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-09-18T11:39:12.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757522/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757522/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757522/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-09-05","Contempt of Court Act 1981","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what recent discussions he has had with social media providers on user postings and the provisions of the Contempt of Court Act 1981.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757523","Attorney General","false","2017-09-11","In July, I launched a Public Legal Education panel to support and drive forward legal education initiatives. Bringing together key organisations will mean a more joined up approach to Public Legal Education and will ensure that more people can reap the benefits of the good work being done.","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2017-09-11T13:45:41.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757523/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757523/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757523/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-09-05","Law: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what steps he is taking to improve public legal education.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757524","Attorney General","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Serious Fraud Office (SFO) has played an important role in the fight against serious and complex fraud, bribery and corruption. Between 2012/13 and 2016/17, 66 defendants were convicted from 94 who were prosecuted giving an overall defendant conviction rate of 70.2%. In terms of cases, 31 were successful out of 36. This gives a case conviction rate of 86.1%. In addition the SFO has concluded four deferred prosecution agreements.</p><p>The SFO also works closely with other justice partners on tackling serious fraud, as well as participating in a number of strategic delivery and working groups.</p><p>The SFO continues to work to improve performance and, following a report by Her Majesty’s Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate (HMCPSI) in May 2016, progress has been made to bolster governance and ensure greater efficiency.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-09-12T07:53:55.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757524/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757524/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757524/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-09-05","Fraud: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the work of the Serious Fraud Office in investigating and securing convictions for fraud offences.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757525","Attorney General","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government re-committed in our manifesto that we will extend the scope of the scheme. As a first step, an extension of the scheme to further terrorism offences came into effect last month. We are considering with the Lord Chancellor how further to fulfil our commitment to extending the scheme.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-09-12T07:43:11.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757525/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757525/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757525/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-09-05","Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the Unduly Lenient Sentences scheme to offences beyond those which are already covered by that scheme.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757526","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T15:04:41.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757526/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757526/answer","UKSA response to 8817 .pdf","UKSA Response to PQ8817","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757526/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Public Sector: Hemsworth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, (a) how many and (b) what proportion of working-age people in Hemsworth constituency worked in the public sector in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757527","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-13","<p>Information about agency staff employed in the Government Property Unit (GPU) since 2010 is not held centrally and would incur disproportionate costs to determine. I can however confirm that two agency staff are currently employed in the GPU.</p><p> </p><p>Our records show that (a) one employee has been seconded into the GPU from outside Government and (b) four employees have served periods of secondment to organisations outside Government, since 2010.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-09-13T14:13:33.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757527/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757527/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757527/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Government Property Unit: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many agency staff have been employed in the Government Property Unit; and how many secondments there have been to that unit from (a) inside and (b) outside government in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757528","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The GCS Knowledge &amp; Capability Unit does not currently recover costs from recipients for projects. The Unit will regularly review funding models to ensure they provide value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T15:08:46.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757528/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757528/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757528/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Government Communication Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government has plans to charge recipients for work done by civil servants working for the Government Communications Service abroad.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757529","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>This information is not collected or held centrally.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-09-12T14:53:59.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757529/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757529/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757529/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Government Communication Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants in the Government Communications Service have been assigned to work on issues relating to the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757530","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Communication Service has been running, in various formats, since its establishment in 1917. The recently published Government Communications Plan 2017/18 provides details of current activities and can be found here <a href="https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/communications-plan/" target="_blank">https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/communications-plan/</a></p><p> </p><p>Since its inception in September 2015, the GCS Knowledge &amp; Capability Unit has completed 5 projects.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T09:14:53.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757530/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757530/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757530/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Government Communication Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many projects the (a) Government Communications Service and (b) Government Communications Service International have completed since inception.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757531","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-12","<p>The Government Communication Service has been running, in various formats, since its establishment in 1917. There are no plans to make the Government Communications Service a new function that fills capacity gaps on priority communications campaigns.</p><p> </p><p>HMG staff can be redeployed across government departments to cover priorities where feasible. The Government Communications Plan was published on 23rd August 2017 and can be found here: <a href="https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/communications-plan/" target="_blank">https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/communications-plan/</a></p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-09-12T09:05:41.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757531/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757531/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757531/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Government Communication Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress has been made on making the Government Communications Service a new function that helps deliver the annual Government Communications Plan by filling in essential roles for priority communications campaigns.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757532","Department for Transport","false","2017-09-13","<p>There are currently two Department for Transport (DfT) civil servants who work solely on High Speed 2 communications and there are two vacancies. None of the civil servants were assigned to their posts by the Government Communications Service, but all of them are employed as civil servants in accordance with GCS standards. In addition, there are two further DfT civil servants who work in part on HS2 communications, but have additional responsibilities covering all the department’s policies.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-09-13T15:06:26.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757532/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757532/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757532/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-09-05","Government Communication Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many civil servants in the Government Communications Service have been assigned to work on issues relating to High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757533","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>Investment decisions within the Parliamentary Contributory Pension Fund (PCPF) are a matter for the Trustees who receive professional advice regarding decisions on the management of scheme assets. Information on the PCPF’s investments is not therefore held centrally. However, details of the scheme’s investments are set out each year in a published Annual Review.</p><p>The Civil Service Pension Scheme is unfunded and as such does not make investments.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-09-11T15:24:56.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757533/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757533/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757533/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the total value of investment is by the (a) Parliamentary Contributory Pensions Fund and (b) Civil Service Pension Scheme in funds linked to freehold ground rents.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","8596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757534","Cabinet Office","false","2017-09-11","<p>I refer the Hon. member to my answer given on 7th September 2017 to PQ7523.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-09-11T14:30:16.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757534/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757534/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757534/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-09-05","Public Sector: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government's race audit findings will be published.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","8638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757535","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>This information is all publicly available on the European Investment Bank (EIB) website. The EIB publishes details of all projects including dates of approval and signature and total signed amounts.</p><p> </p><p>Information on UK projects can be found in the link below.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.eib.org/projects/loan/list/?region=1&amp;country=GB" target="_blank">http://www.eib.org/projects/loan/list/?region=1&amp;country=GB</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-09-11T14:26:59.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757535/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757535/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757535/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","European Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many new projects in the UK have been (a) signed-off and (b) financed by the European Investment Bank in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","8669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757536","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>If there have been insurance claims made on Pool Re after a terror attack, Pool Re must notify the Treasury. Following this notification, the Treasury has 21 working days to certify if the event constituted an act of terrorism under the 1993 Reinsurance Act.</p><p> </p><p>The Treasury has followed this process and responded within the 21 day period in certifying 3 terrorist attacks in 2017. The Treasury follows an established legal process to do this, recognising the urgency of responding to requests and treating this as a matter of priority.</p><p> </p><p>We remain in discussion with the insurance industry, Pool Re and other interested parties to make sure that the 1993 Reinsurance Act continues to enable appropriate terrorism cover to be available for businesses in the UK.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-09-11T14:26:10.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757536/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757536/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757536/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans his Department has to update the 1993 Reinsurance Act and the process of certifying terror attacks.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","8601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757537","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>HMRC expects to publish the post-implementation review of real time information later this year.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-11T15:56:07.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757537/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757537/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757537/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","PAYE","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to publish the post-implementation review of PAYE Real Time Information.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","8609"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757538","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-11T15:59:55.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757538/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757538/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757538/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Treasury: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many procurements undertaken by his Department have taken more than (a) three months, (b) six months, (c) one year and (d) two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757539","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>As of 31<sup>st</sup> August HMRC has paid £3,335.20 in compensation to customers.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-11T13:01:35.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757539/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757539/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757539/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department has paid from the public purse in compensation for errors relating to (a) tax-free and (b) 30 hours of free childcare; and what estimate he has made of how much will be paid out in total for such errors.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","8693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757540","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Government recognises the cultural and economic contribution historic homes make right across the UK. Heritage Maintenance Funds play an important role in keeping historic homes in the best possible condition and making them accessible for the general public. That is why assets placed in Heritage Maintenance Funds continue to receive a complete exemption from inheritance tax.</p><p> </p><p>The Treasury regularly monitors all reliefs and exemptions, including Heritage Maintenance Funds, to ensure they continue to be appropriate and affordable.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-11T16:04:46.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757540/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757540/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757540/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Historic Buildings: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of Heritage Maintenance Funds; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","8700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757541","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>Parents who reported technical issues during the application process were provided with a 30 hours code manually. Those parents who are eligible, and applied before 31 August will be given a code that will allow them to access 30 hours free childcare for the September term.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-09-11T11:38:20.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757541/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757541/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757541/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many potentially eligible parents were unable to access their eligibility codes for their 30 hours of free childcare due to technical issues with the site administered by HM Revenue and Customs.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","8694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757542","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The income that HM Treasury’s core department has received from sub-letting on its estate between financial years 2010/11 and 2016/17 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>10/11</p></td><td><p>11/12</p></td><td><p>12/13</p></td><td><p>13/14</p></td><td><p>14/15</p></td><td><p>15/16</p></td><td><p>16/17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£0.6m</p></td><td><p>£2.8m</p></td><td><p>£10.8m</p></td><td><p>£13.1m</p></td><td><p>£14.0m</p></td><td><p>£14.0m</p></td><td><p>£15.2m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>HM Treasury’s core department did not incur letting fees payable to agents in the course of sub-letting its estate over the relevant period.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","8785","2017-09-11T16:36:47.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757542/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757542/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757542/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Treasury: Sub-letting","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department has received from sub-lets on its estate in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757543","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The government has agreed to commission a detailed consultative report on the impact of VAT and APD on tourism in Northern Ireland to recommend how best to build upon the growing success of that sector.</p><p> </p><p>Further details on the report will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-11T15:52:30.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757543/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757543/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757543/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Tourism: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress the Government has made on its consultation report on the effect of VAT on tourism in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","8880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757544","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-12","<p>Whilst it is not possible under current EU laws to exempt from VAT all purchases of defibrillators, the government does maintain several VAT reliefs to aid purchases of defibrillators. These include VAT refunds of purchases made by local authorities and VAT relief for purchases made through voluntary contributions which are donated to eligible charities or the NHS.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-12T10:43:00.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757544/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757544/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757544/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Defibrillators: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to exempt automated external defibrillators from VAT.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","8849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757545","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-13","<p>The Valuation Office Agency (VOA) is responsible for assessing Rateable Values for business rates. Since Automatic Teller Machines (ATMs) came into existence, the VOA has separately assessed sites for them wherever a) it is aware of them and b) they meet the test of being in rateable occupation under the relevant legislation and case law.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-13T16:30:46.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757545/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757545/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757545/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Cash Dispensing: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 17 July 2017 to Question 4658, whether the Government carried out any research or assessment before deciding to levy business rates on cash machines; and for what reasons and by whom that decision was taken to levy those rates.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","8846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757546","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-13","<p>Payments made by an employer for an employee’s image rights are taxable and the appropriate treatment has been set out in guidelines by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). The guidance is clear that payments that are, in reality, earnings cannot be treated as image rights payments.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC enforces the image rights rules and has a project looking specifically at compliance risks in football to ensure that football clubs, players, managers and agents pay the correct amount of tax. Since 2014-15 HMRC has brought in over £260m by tackling non-compliance in football.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-09-13T16:31:35.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757546/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757546/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757546/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Taxation: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what potential effect treating payments to employees derived from image rights as earnings subject to taxation would have on the public purse.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757547","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-13","<p>The government has made no assessment of the impact of reducing fuel duty rates to these levels.</p><p> </p><p>At current exchange rates, the UK fuel duty rate on petrol is already lower than that applied in France.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-13T15:30:47.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757547/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757547/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757547/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Excise Duties: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the economy of a reduction in UK fuel duty to (a) the EU average, (b) an equivalent rate to that used in France and (c) an equivalent rate to that used in Luxembourg; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757548","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-13","<p>The European Commission collates figures for fuel duty from each of the Member States once a year. Information on fuel duty rates over the past 5 years can be found at the following links. While fuel duty is levied in local currency, the EC figures convert these into euros, using the prevailing exchange rates at the date of publication.</p><p> </p><p>2017: https://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/sites/taxation/files/resources/documents/taxation/excise_duties/energy_products/rates/excise_duties-part_ii_energy_products_en.pdf</p><p> </p><p>2016: https://circabc.europa.eu/sd/a/58bf9e30-7bdd-4a29-9bb2-4a62c542f1d1/EDT-Ref%201045%20(II-Energy)%20-%20January%202016.pdf</p><p>2015: https://circabc.europa.eu/sd/a/bba65b10-5803-41f6-abd5-9be8490d36b6/EDT-Ref%201042%20(II-Energy)%20-%20January%202015</p><p> </p><p>2014: https://circabc.europa.eu/sd/a/f52da286-1c43-401e-bbb8-11132b349880/II-Energy_July2014%20final.pdf</p><p> </p><p>2013: https://circabc.europa.eu/sd/a/ee2fb487-3c8c-468e-80f7-e89393a4477a/II-Energy_January2013_final.pdf</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-09-13T13:52:21.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757548/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757548/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757548/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Excise Duties: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the fuel duty differential between the UK and each of the other 27 member states of the EU has been for each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","8825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757549","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The income that HM Treasury’s core department has received from sub-letting on its estate between financial years 2010/11 and 2016/17 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>10/11</p></td><td><p>11/12</p></td><td><p>12/13</p></td><td><p>13/14</p></td><td><p>14/15</p></td><td><p>15/16</p></td><td><p>16/17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£0.6m</p></td><td><p>£2.8m</p></td><td><p>£10.8m</p></td><td><p>£13.1m</p></td><td><p>£14.0m</p></td><td><p>£14.0m</p></td><td><p>£15.2m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>HM Treasury’s core department did not incur letting fees payable to agents in the course of sub-letting its estate over the relevant period.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","8747","2017-09-11T16:36:47.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757549/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757549/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757549/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Treasury: Sub-letting","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department has paid in letting fees for its estate in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","8785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757550","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Treasury is responsible for the Help to Buy: ISA and mortgage guarantee schemes; the Department for Communities and Local Government have responsibility for the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme.</p><p>Both Department’s routinely publishes information on the take-up and the total value of support provided through the Help to Buy schemes.</p><p>From the introduction of the Help to Buy: ISA on 1 December 2015 to 31 March 2017, the total value of bonuses paid was £54m. Further information is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/official-statistics-on-the-help-to-buy-isa-scheme" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/official-statistics-on-the-help-to-buy-isa-scheme</a></p><p>Between the launch of the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme on 1 April 2013 to 31 March 2017, the total value of equity loans provided through scheme was £5.86bn. Further information is available at: <a href="https://help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2017/" target="_blank">https://help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2017</a></p><p>The Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme was designed to be self-financing through the commercial fee that lenders paid for the provision of the Government guarantee. The fee was set to cover the administration cost, the cost of capital of providing the guarantee and expected losses from loans guaranteed under the scheme. Further information is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/621112/H2B_MGS_Official_Statistics_Publication_June_17.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/621112/H2B_MGS_Official_Statistics_Publication_June_17.pdf</a></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","8946","2017-09-11T14:34:54.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757550/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757550/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-09-05","Help to Buy Scheme: Individual Savings Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost has been to the public purse of the Help to Buy ISA policy since the introduction of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","8945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757551","HM Treasury","false","2017-09-11","<p>The Treasury is responsible for the Help to Buy: ISA and mortgage guarantee schemes; the Department for Communities and Local Government have responsibility for the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme.</p><p>Both Department’s routinely publishes information on the take-up and the total value of support provided through the Help to Buy schemes.</p><p>From the introduction of the Help to Buy: ISA on 1 December 2015 to 31 March 2017, the total value of bonuses paid was £54m. Further information is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/official-statistics-on-the-help-to-buy-isa-scheme" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/official-statistics-on-the-help-to-buy-isa-scheme</a></p><p>Between the launch of the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme on 1 April 2013 to 31 March 2017, the total value of equity loans provided through scheme was £5.86bn. Further information is available at: <a href="https://help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2017/" target="_blank">https://help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-and-help-to-buy-newbuy-statistics-april-2013-to-march-2017</a></p><p>The Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme was designed to be self-financing through the commercial fee that lenders paid for the provision of the Government guarantee. The fee was set to cover the administration cost, the cost of capital of providing the guarantee and expected losses from loans guaranteed under the scheme. Further information is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/621112/H2B_MGS_Official_Statistics_Publication_June_17.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/621112/H2B_MGS_Official_Statistics_Publication_June_17.pdf</a></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","8945","2017-09-11T14:34:54.287Z",,"http://da