ment.uk/resources/757555/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757555/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757555/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-05","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 5 September 2017 to Question 5844, what benefits resulted from the provision of £19 million to local authorities tackle tenancy fraud.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","8971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757556","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-14","<p>I can confirm that a response was sent to a Salvation Army letter regarding our plans for the funding reforms for supported housing on Tuesday 5 September.</p><p>Developing a workable and sustainable funding model for supported housing is a priority for the Government.</p><p>We will set out further details on our plans in the autumn.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-14T14:30:30.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757556/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757556/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757556/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-05","Salvation Army: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to respond to the representations made by the Salvation Army on the effect of universal credit on the Salvation Army's provision of supported housing.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757557","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-14","<p>Domestic abuse is a devastating crime and we are determined to ensure that victims, regardless of their circumstances, receive the support they need when they need it.</p><p>Refuges provide a critical bedrock of support for victims of domestic abuse and their families.</p><p>Since 2014, we have invested over £33.5 million in services to support victims of domestic abuse, including refuges.</p><p>Local authorities in Gloucestershire have benefitted from this funding during the same period. They have used the funding to provide refuges, specialist accommodation-based support, community and outreach services to ensure no victims of domestic abuse is turned away from the support they need.</p><p>The funding is also being used to provide dedicated support to victims from minority communities and their families in the Gloucestershire area.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-14T14:36:37.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757557/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757557/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757557/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-05","Refuges: Gloucestershire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure the increase in provision of refuges in Gloucestershire.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757558","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-14","<p>Local authorities in England were offered a four year funding deal from 2016-17, which 97 per cent of authorities, including Stroud District Council, accepted. The 2016-17 Local Government Finance Settlement allocated Revenue Support Grant by looking at the main resources available to councils, taking account of funding that councils can raise locally, namely council tax and business rates. This ensured that councils delivering the same set of services received the same percentage change in the funding available to provide those services.</p><p>The local government finance settlement is subject to an annual statutory consultation exercise, offering an opportunity each year to consider representations from all authorities.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-14T14:33:18.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757558/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757558/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-05","Local Government Finance: Stroud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to reassess the level of funding to be reclaimed from Stroud District Council as a result of changes to council tax and rent support arrangements.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757559","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-09-12","<p>We have replaced the Department for Work and Pension's Temporary Accommodation Management Fee with a Flexible Homelessness Support Grant which local authorities can use more strategically to prevent and tackle homelessness. This amounts to £402 million over the two years from 2017/18.</p><p>The funding has been allocated according to a formula which reflects relative homeless pressures and the cost of using the private rented sector to meet them.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-09-12T10:44:24.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757559/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757559/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/757559/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-09-05","Homelessness: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to support rural local authorities in the provision of emergency accommodation for homelessness cases.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","8969"
